spanGrp.span: We go downhill all the way to the school.
Se damĩũ-lo-mĩ dieska kerrawã (_) yabla yunã-glö se damĩũ-lo
We get there and uh… go by uh… we take that road
Jeska ele damãu eee… se të je guge-ra-wã
and get to where there is a huge tree.
Se damĩũ jeska kal kate tã'ĩ
Then there is the Ceibo River which goes all the way.
Tögapa diglö Rio Ceibo kögẽu kögẽu kögẽu ra
Uh… there is something to go up and down.
Ele jirö kate yu-lë jirö köjö-glöũ juigweta wagweta
We go uh… there is a huge tree
Se damĩũ estee… kal kate grande
and we get to the road going in that direction, to Santa Maria.
je je damĩũ se damĩũ (_) ñala mãu jamĩgweta rö Santa_Maria
We go on and on till there is a big place;
Se damãũ-lo se damãũ-lo kã' blali tã'ĩ
we go by the side of the Chululi Creek and go up.
se damãũ-lo dia bi Chöluli köska se damãũ juigweta
People live there and the road takes you to Salitre.
Jeska pe-wa sẽr-gẽ jamĩ mãu-lo Salitre
We go on and on uh… by the pinapple plantation;
Se damãũ-lo se damãũ-lo ele… piña kö jãrga
by Cabagra, Boruca, Terraba and Salitre
uh...there are many other people around there;
ee je kenẽwa (_) tã'ĩ siga-wa tsõ
there are many houses far away.
Many whites come up here, but those living up here are Indians.’
Maleska-wa rö sikwa bötö-gẽ juigweta rö Indio-wa
